Ask HN: How did you become good enough at understanding and doing mathematics?
text:
Hoping to hear about your personalised journey of learning mathematics. Doesn't matter if you were a math major or not.

Which topics did you learn and in what order? Any specific books or topics that helped you tremendously?

How did you become comfortable in reading mathy things (proofs) and understanding them or apply math to model real world problems?
